lobal Television Network]]\n*[[Nick Hector]], film editor\n*[[Helix (band)|Helix]], heavy metal band\n*[[Derek Hines]], jazz vocalist\n*[[Kathryn Ladano]], bass clarinetist and composer\n*[[Lisa LaFlamme]], television news anchor, [[CTV Television Network]]\n*[[Glenn Lewis]], [[neo soul]] singer-songwriter\n*[[Paul MacLeod]], singer-songwriter\n*[[Master T]], television and radio personality, [[MuchMusic]]\n*[[Lois Maxwell]], actress\n*[[Messenjah]], reggae band\n*[[Danny Michel]], musician\n*[[Edwin Outwater]], conductor, [[Kitchener\u2013Waterloo Symphony]]\n*[[Jeremy Ratchford]], actor\n*[[Steve Strongman]], blues guitarist\n*[[Rob Szabo]], music producer and performer\n*[[Tasha the Amazon]], hip hop musician\n*[[Homer Watson]], landscape artist\n*[[Dawud Wharnsby]], singer-songwriter, poet, and performer\n\n===Politics===\n*[[Louis Orville Breithaupt]], 18th Lieutenant-Governor of Ontario (1952\u20131957)\n*[[William Lyon Mackenzie King]], Canada's tenth, and longest serving, Prime Minister\n*[[Michael Kraus (minister)|Michael Kraus]], minister and entrepreneur\n*[[Judy Wasylycia-Leis]], [[New Democratic Party (Canada)|NDP]] member of the Canadian House of Commons\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n===Notes===\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{wikivoyage|Kitchener}}\n* [http://www.kitchener.ca/ Official website]\n\n{{Geographic location  <!-- This geo box is for DIRECTLY ADJACENT municipalities as standardized for all other municipalities -->\n | Centre    = Kitchener\n | North     = [[Woolwich, Ontario|Woolwich]]\n | Northeast =\n | East      = [[Cambridge, Ontario|Cambridge]]\n | Southeast =\n | South     = [[North Dumfries, Ontario|North Dumfries]]\n | Southwest =\n | West      = [[Wilmot, Ontario|Wilmot]]\n | Northwest = [[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]]\n}}\n{{Kitchener, Ontario}}\n{{WaterlooRegion}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Kitchener, Ontario| ]]\n[[Category:Lower-tier municipalities in Ontario]]\n[[Category:German Canadian]]\n", "name_user": "1980fast", "label": "safe", "comment": "Caption punctuation adjustment, per WP:CAPFRAG", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kitchener,_Ontario"}
{"title_page": "Agency", "text_new": "{{wiktionary|agency}}\n\n'''Agency''' may refer to:\n* a governmental or other [[institution]]\n* the abstract principle that autonomous beings, agents, are capable of acting by themselves; see [[autonomy]]\n\n{{tocright}}\n== Abstract principle ==\n* [[Agency (law)]], a person acting on behalf of another person\n* [[Agency (LDS Church)]], \"the privilege of choice... introduced by God\"\n* [[Agency (moral)]], capacity for making moral judgments\n* [[Agency (philosophy)]], the capacity of an autonomous agent to act, relating to action theory in philosophy\n*[[Agency (psychology)]], the ability to recognize or attribute agency in humans and non-human animals\n* [[Agency (sociology)]], the ability of social actors to make independent choices, relating to action theory in sociology\n* [[Agency and structure]], ability of an individual to organize future situations and resource distribution\n\n== Organizations ==\n{{hatnote|For fictional agencies, see {{slink||Arts, entertainment, and media}}}}\n* [[Advertising agency]], a service business dedicated to creating, planning and handling advertising for its clients\n* [[Employment agency]], a business that serves as a representative, acting on behalf of another\n* [[Government agency]], a department of a local or national government responsible for the oversight and administration of a specific function\n* [[International agency]], an inter-governmental body\n* [[Marketing agency]], a service business dedicated to creating, planning and handling marketing for its clients\n* [[News agency]]\n* The Agency, a nickname for the [[Central Intelligence Agency]]\n*[http://brandchanakya.in/ Digital Marketing Agency]\n\n== Places ==\n* [[Agency (country subdivision)]]\n* [[Agency, Iowa]], US\n* [[Agency, Missouri]], US\n* [[Agency, Montana]], US\n* [[Agency Township (disambiguation)]], name of townships in four US states\n\n==Arts, entertainment, and media ==\n* [[Agency (novel)|''Agency'' (novel)]], a science fiction novel by William Gibson\n* [[The Agency (2001 TV series)|''The Agency'' (2001 TV series)]],\n* [[The Agency (2007 TV series)|''The Agency'' (2007 TV series)]]\n* [[The Agency (comics)|''The Agency'' (comics)]]\n* [[The Agency (film)|''The Agency'' (film)]], a 1980 Canadian film starring Lee Majors\n* The Agency, name of the fictional secret government organization in the 2000 TV series ''[[The Invisible Man (2000 TV series)#The Agency|The Invisible Man]]''\n* ''[[The Agency: Covert Ops]]'', a spy-themed massively multiplayer online shooter video game\n* ''[[Morgana Robinson's The Agency]]'', a 2016 British TV mockumentary\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Agent (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Free agency (disambiguation)]]\n\n{{disambiguation|geo}}\n", "text_old": "{{wiktionary|agency}}\n\n'''Agency''' may refer to:\n* a governmental or other [[institution]]\n* the abstract principle that autonomous beings, agents, are capable of acting by themselves; see [[autonomy]]\n\n{{tocright}}\n== Abstract principle ==\n* [[Agency (law)]], a person acting on behalf of another person\n* [[Agency (LDS Church)]], \"the privilege of choice... introduced by God\"\n* [[Agency (moral)]], capacity for making moral judgments\n* [[Agency (philosophy)]], the capacity of an autonomous agent to act, relating to action theory in philosophy\n*[[Agency (psychology)]], the ability to recognize or attribute agency in humans and non-human animals\n* [[Agency (sociology)]], the ability of social actors to make independent choices, relating to action theory in sociology\n* [[Agency and structure]], ability of an individual to organize future situations and resource distribution\n\n== Organizations ==\n{{hatnote|For fictional agencies, see {{slink||Arts, entertainment, and media}}}}\n* [[Advertising agency]], a service business dedicated to creating, planning and handling advertising for its clients\n* [[Employment agency]], a business that serves as a representative, acting on behalf of anoth